HEADWORD: Pickle-herring
<hw>Pic"kle-her"ring</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
herring preserved in brine; a pickled herring.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A merry-andrew; a buffoon.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pickler</ent>⟦br⟧
